criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Is a caregiver of a child in kindergarten, 1st, 2nd or 3rd grade at a participating
             school (i.e.,"target child");

          -  The target child lives with the caregiver at least half of the time;

          -  The caregiver speaks English or Spanish;

          -  The caregiver is listed as one of the target child's parents/guardians in the school's
             records.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  The target child is in a self-contained classroom due to cognitive or emotional
             disabilities;

          -  The caregiver is a kindergarten, 1st, 2nd or 3rd grade teacher at a participating
             school;

          -  The target child attended one of the participating schools during a previous cohort of
             the study;

          -  The caregiver is participating in a competing parenting program at the school, the
             "Intensive Family Literacy program".
